    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-31T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="484"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.53/138: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-31T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 31, 1943—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 31—5:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5741. Eden today handed me the text of agreement and annexes reached with the
                    Portuguese authorities for the use of Portuguese facilities in the Azores by
                    United Kingdom aircraft and military and naval forces. Agreement is dated August
                    17 and use of facilities specified will begin as from 8th October, 1943.<note
                        n="67" xml:id="d484fn67">For text of the agreement, see <hi rend="italic"
                            >British and Foreign State Papers</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >cxlvi</hi>, p. 447.</note>
                </p>
                <p>For reasons of security am arranging to despatch this text by special courier on
                    Army bomber expected to leave September 1st.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
